Gwyn -- it's The International Association for Philosophy an Literature
(IAPL)'s 20th anniversary conference called DRAMAS OF CULTURE, taking
place from May 7 to 11 right where you are. The program is too thick to
type up, feels like a mini-MLA, but you should be able to get one right
there & I doubt that it's booked up or out. (for more information you
could call Campus Information [703 993-2090] or the Conference
Coordinator, John Foster at 703 993-2774 or email him: jfoster@gmu.edu.
 
Note, however, one of the panels, meeting on Thursday 9-12 a.m. in the
Movie Theatre (inneresting place!) on the Ground Floor, & moderated by
yours truly: THE ECHO OF THE ORIGINAL: TRANSLATION AS ARENA FOR THE DRAMA
OF CULTURE with Charles Bernstein, Ann Leatherwood, Suzanne Jill Levine,
Howard Norman & Andrew Schelling.
 
Also, for those in DC area, the previous evening, Wednesday at 8 pm,
Bernstein & Joris will be reading at Rod Smith's bookshop.
 
Pierre
