Susan, did you stay at the writer's cottage up above the wharfs?
 
I read at the Salamanca Festival (fringe) in 91 so it's great to hear it
mentioned.  I agree that the whole of Australian writing is ignored by the
States' distributors; Carmel Bird's name appeared on the back pages of Best
Short Stories of 91 but it's impossible to find her work in print over here
(few years back I did find "Woodpecker Point" but nothing since).  Check
out Mark Robert's work on the Aus. Writers on Line (AWOL) webpage and
electronic bookshop.  http://www.ozemail.com.au/~awol/bookshop1.html .
You'll find your mates there.
 
This may be the only way.
 
