not sure if this is of help, but Dick Higgins, former fluxus activist,
publisher (something else press), poet and scholar is THE authority on
pattern poems, or concrete poetry; he did a study of George Herbert's
pattern poems (he of "The Altar") and did a larger work on the history of
pattern poems, which i believe was published by Southern Illinois
University Press in paperback about six years ago.
 
