I suspect that the book on Francis Bacon, title of which Baratier was trying
to come up with, was "Francis Bacon & the Loss of Self," by Ernst van Alphen,
smart young Nederlandish literary scholar; UK edition, Reaktion Books, 1992,
don't know about the US edition.  Good as it is, I'm not sure it's all that
relevant to the current thread: has more to do with narrative than with the
visual in poetry.
