Just back from the Beckett festival in Victoria. Saw 21 plays! Heard a lot
of papers, but the papers were not as interesting as the productions. For
me the highlight was Fred Neumann's performance in _Worstward Ho_. Of
course, one is lucky to see it, because he is so good, and because other
actors are afraid to do it because Neumann has sett his stamp on it.
Contorski was there with his Beckett haircut and too-short pants, nice
touch, that.
 
