From:         George Bowering <bowering@SFU.CA>
Subject:      Re: writing through
 
Last week while at the Beckett conference I couldnt do number two. I sat
there and sat there, saying "I can't go. I'll go." Only when I got home did
I go out to compost the garden , squatted there for a while, and moved
around, managing to spell out three longish words. Is that called writing
through the body?
 
"Toujours est-il que je redoute le signal de l'horrible petite trompette."
