    This discussion between Aldon N. And B. Holman
    about being not about
    to be about or not to be about
    -------
    I don't think Bob was saying that
    poems that aren't ABOUT something don't have any meaning....
    but what he meant by ABOUT was a very particular kind of "aboutness"
    ______
    It can't be "about" things like "consciousness" or "words"
    as much as rootedness, in place or ethnic identity, and there
    must be some kind of thematic consistency, PIN DOWNable....
    easily.......
    ______
    though pop songs are sometimes more of a challenge
    than wild "out there" "free improv....."
    ------
