From:         Maria Damon <MDamon9999@AOL.COM>
Subject:      Re: Larry Levis
 
thanks maz for the eulogy and poem.  never heard of levis before, but now i
have and am glad.  esp to hear of someone else whose mother's called selma.
went to a funeral myself this a.m., and heard a 10 yr old girl read a poem to
her dad whose 34 yr old dad's car crashed a coupla mornings ago, and he went
up in the fiery wreckage..."I sit here in grief, listening with
disbelief...daddy daddy why'd you leave?  daddy daddy come back please."  it
was...poetic.  i didn't know the guy he was a friend of friends and i went
cuz they wanted to show up in my car instead of their own work truck.
