Subject:      Re: formal continuum/conspicuous repetition (fwd)
 
I am surprised at the interest in "counting" as form. Form is plainly
what anyone is or is not in, when they write--- on a good day, so to speak ---
 when things go right --- as with any other sport. Counting is no
more a measure of success in writing than checking out the golden
mean and other similar proportional divisions in a painting is a
meausre of anything except the goofiness of the measurer.
 
Tony Green,
e-mail: t.green@auckland.ac.nz
