Tom Beard,
 
"Querzblatz" (although "quertz-" is an acceptable variant spelling) has
absolutely no meaning nor etymology whatsoever. I made it up. It is
supposed to accomodate the poetries and poetics that words like
"experimental," "avant-garde," "language," "innovative" (although that
last may come closest) don't cover; I was tired of not having a word. It
has Q and Z in it because those are the letters not on the telephone
dial, and they sound cool.
 
Gwyn McVay
