Date:         Wed, 15 May 1996 11:20:40 EDT
Reply-To:     UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         John Whiting <100707.731@COMPUSERVE.COM>
Subject:      Re: quertzblatz
 
Gwyn McVay says:
 
". . . quertzblatz . . . has absolutely no meaning . . ."
 
What? I was just writing an essay explaining that it was an
expletive first used by a German philologist learning to touch-
type. You have no right to say it is meaningless; it no longer
belongs to you. As soon as a sound is uttered or an arrangement
of letters is placed upon a page and others assign it a sense,
it goes straight into God's Dictionary. Is "chortle" nonsense
just because Lewis Caroll so intended? If you want to invent a
meaningless word, best keep it to yourself.
 
John Whiting
Diatribal Press
London
