   me too. What does Maria mean by this meaning, meaning as value?
   Since I read both "traditional" and "non-traditional" (i'm not defining
   that now) verse (in terms of "form"), I guess I'm curious what form
   attracts me and why. But I guess I feel that "meaning" tends to get
   pushed aside, in such discussions. As if the meaning of the form matters
   more than the meaning on a more content level. If I see the MEANING
   of say a Berrigan poem as similar to the meaning of a Shakespeare sonnet
   (and i don't mean a SINGULAR meaning, but a kind of meaning-complex),
   am I being a bad boy who has not eaten enough of my post-modern peas
   and recognized how IMPORTANT the formal differences are in the fashion-
   show of life? cs
