Date:         Fri, 17 May 1996 17:14:04 EDT
Reply-To:     UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
Sender:       UB Poetics discussion group <POETICS@UBVM.CC.BUFFALO.EDU>
From:         John Whiting <100707.731@COMPUSERVE.COM>
Subject:      Re: sometimes an informal Cage comes
Comments: To: Rod Smith <AERIALEDGE@AOL.COM>
 
Cage certainly allowed for improvisation within the established
parameters of the Four Songs he wrote for Electric Phoenix (SATB
quartet plus electronics). He attended our first rehearsal at my
studio in London and gave his approval to our rather free-wheeling
approach; his only caveat was that the singers shouldn't listen to
each other. His droll recognition of the groups' character was
contained in his final note of instruction: "A virtuosic performance
is invited." He got it!
 
John Whiting
October Sound (my other hat)
London
=========================================================================
