Re: Beethoven's melodies. I believe the issue of ownership of melody
was not raised until about a decade or so after Beethoven's death. No
one thought -- at least this is my understanding -- that a melody was
owned by anybody, constitued what we now call "intellectual property."
 
Tom Mandel
