Dear Dave,
 
Is it the word 'saussure' to which you object? The other part of the quote
looks pretty intelligent from here, unless of course you don't think poems
set up separate structures, or you don't think meaning operates in
differences. Mainly it's monotony I object to, as opposed to repetition,
which is the basis of music, no? Monotony then would mean repetition
without surprise.
 
