This is a product endorsement.  The Mac Low, Duncan and Waldrop books are
all beautiful examples of fine printing, as well as good reads, and these
are bargain basement prices. The trade editions are all excellent. I don't
wish to single out any one out of these books at the expense of the others
but, if you're not already familiar with the work of Karen MacCormack (whose
work deserves to be more widely known than I suspect it is), _Quirks &
Quillets_ is a worthy introduction.
 
Best,
Jonathan
 
