From:         Marjorie Perloff <perloff@LELAND.STANFORD.EDU>
Subject:      Re Refereed Journals
In-Reply-To:  <199605230407.AAA00160@listserv.acsu.buffalo.edu>
 
I agree that anonymous submissions (as in PMLA) are obnoxious but Ron, I
wonder if you really mean what you're saying.  I serve on a lot of
editorial boards and, for instance, on CONTEMPORARY LITERATURE I think the
process is extremely fair.  All "refereed" means is that particular
members of the board are sent an article to evaluate and their reports
then go to the editors in chief.  But I take it that Social Text doesn't
even bother with that-- they just commission articles.  Which means no one
outside the little clique gets in.  Do you really think that's optimal?
 
I think the best and liveliest journals are more open than that.
 
 
Marjorie Perloff
