Subject:      Re: eniacs
 
this is Rid speaking:
 
My main point, & this is where the defense of Ross comes in-- The "point" of
Ross's last book can be summed up thusly-- that corporate culture operates
out of the assumption that there isn't enough to go around. It seems more
than reasonable to question this assumption. As long as "the game wins" most
of us won't. This is what you won't find much, or any discussion of at NYT &
co. So given the relative power of Social Text vs the times it's important, I
think, to ask why _this_ issue for the Times & not another.
 
The discussion on this list so far wld not be that different had the Sokal
story been on the cover of AWP.
 
