Caroline,
 
I just picked up a copy of _Marine Snow_ at Talking Leaves bookstore in
Buffalo for $12.00 (US). You can order by mail from Talking Leaves. I've
misplaced the store's address but maybe somebody in Buffalo can provide it.
Of course, it was probably the store's only copy, so you might be better off
going directly to the press as Charles suggested.
 
My copy of MacCormack's _Quill Driver_ (Nightwood Editions, probably
available from SPD) has neither a publication date nor a copyright date in
it. I think it came out between _Straw Cupid_ and _Quirks & Quillets_, but
it might be more recent. If you don't already have them, I highly recommend
them also.
 
I just got back from a camping trip or I would have responded sooner.
 
