Rob (possibly the wrong Rob, for all I know) Hardin
 
PS:  If you're in NYC this summer, come see "Tableau"--poss. at Jackie
60--a play that Colin and I wrote to illustrate our curriculum for The
University for Combating Degenerate Aesthetics. We drive our points home
with several aesthetically-rewarding decapitation scenes--all simulated,
of course.
 
A further aesthetic note: At the end of the play, we write
*I Am Fun* across the bellies of students who prove too weak to
survive. Such are the charms of deadly Darwinian aesthetics.
 
