From:         Joe Aimone <joaimone@UCDAVIS.EDU>
Subject:      "A Sonnet" - take two or three
 
(with apologies to the other Joe A)
 
This is "A Sonnet," a sonnet. This is
a "sonnet"  - - Is this a Sonnet? Is this
This? Is a sonnet a sonnet? This is.
A sonnet is this: a sonnet. Is this
this? Sonnet is. A sonnet, this, is. (A
Is A!) This sonnet is a this. Sonnet
this: sonnet is _a_ sonnet. This. Is a
is a this? Sonnet is a this-sonnet.
This, a sonnet, is a sonnet this is.
Is a sonnet this is a sonnet? This
this a sonnet? Is a sonnet this? Is
is a sonnet this is? A sonnet this
is, this, a sonnet, is this, a sonnet.
This is a sonnet: this is a sonnet.
--
Joe Aimone
Department of English
University of California, Davis
joaimone@ucdavis.edu
