Subject:      Re: Nonset form
 
came across this rereading Creeley's _Autobiography_ (pg. 95)--
 
". . . When young, I'd written Olson with almost pious exclamation: 'Form is
never more than an extension of content.' Now I might say equally, 'Content
is never more than an extension of form.' It depends, as they say in New
England. Back of it all I hear Williams again, saying all those years ago,
'Why don't we tell them that it's _fun_. . .' "
